This paper presents a new approach to Bayesian reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI) that deals with decision-making in uncertain environments. The paper also discusses the use of partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs) to model the learning task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of POMDPs and decision-making in uncertain environments could also place the paper under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves probabilistic modeling and sampling techniques, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
